-- Hornets Break Nine-Game Losing Streak With 93-67 Win Over Magic
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-01-28T05:33:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-28/hornets-break-nine-game-losing-streak-with-93-67-win-over-magic.html
Reserve Carl Landry scored 17 points
to help the  New Orleans Hornets  break their nine-game losing
streak with a 93-67 victory over the Orlando Magic in a National
Basketball Association contest.  Marco Belinelli had 15 points and Jason Smith scored 14 for
the Hornets on their home court at New Orleans Arena.  Dwight Howard  had 28 points and 16 rebounds for his 15th
double-double of the season for the Magic, who turned over the
ball 23 times while shooting 39 percent from the floor.  The Hornets (4-15) are last in the Western Conference’s
five-team Southwest Division, 7 ½ games behind the leading San
Antonio Spurs and Dallas Mavericks. Orlando (12-7) is in third
place in the Eastern Conference’s five-team Southeast Division,
two games behind the  Miami Heat .  To contact the reporter on this story:
